      <description>Follow-up to the previous post: the RVIA (Recreation Vehicle Industry Association) recently reported a positive upwards trend in RV sales. The RVIA doesn&amp;#8217;t track retail sales directly. It surveys the RV manufacturers and reports wholesale figures. The most recent numbers are from May 2010 About 24,400 units were sold in that month. That&amp;#8217;s the 10th [...]&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.rvsleuth.com/positive-industrytrends/"&gt;Positive industry trends&lt;/a&gt; is a post from &lt;a href="http://www.rvsleuth.com"&gt;RV Sleuth&lt;/a&gt;, which teaches RVers how to get the RVs they want for big discounts.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/rv-sleuth/RV_Sleuth-Positive_industry_trends.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Follow-up to the previous post: the RVIA (Recreation Vehicle Industry Association) recently reported a positive upwards trend in <a class="ld_link" href="/rv-sales" target=" " title="RV sales">RV sales</a>.</p>
<p>The RVIA doesn&#8217;t track retail sales directly. It surveys the <a class="ld_link" href="/rv-manufacturers" target=" " title="RV manufacturers">RV manufacturers</a> and reports wholesale figures.</p>
<p>The most recent numbers are from May 2010  About 24,400 units were sold in that month. That&#8217;s the 10th month in a row of upwards trending.</p>
<p>For perspective, May&#8217;s shipments were 84 percent higher than the same month last year. On a seasonally adjusted basis, it&#8217;s an increase of 6 percent over April.</p>
<p>Motorhomes had the highest percentage gain in sales. This probably reflects the growing confidence in the economy. </p>
<p>Since towable represent the larger part of the market, they had a higher volume increase even though their percentage gain was lower. </p>
<p>In 2010 so far (through May), total RV shipments were 108,900 units. That&#8217;s a gain of 91.1 percent (!) compared to this same period last year.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rvsleuth.com/positive-industrytrends/">Positive industry trends</a> is a post from <a href="http://www.rvsleuth.com">RV Sleuth</a>, which teaches RVers how to get the RVs they want for big discounts.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
